<HEADLINE> Tung Chee Hwa Returns to Hong Kong After Australia, New Zealand Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Chief Executive of the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region (SAR) Tung Chee Hwa flew back to
Hong Kong on Friday night after a five-day visit to Australia and
New Zealand.
</P>
<P>
Speaking in a media session after he arrived at the Kai Tak
Airport, Tung said that he had "achieved the desired results"
during the trip, which brought him to Sydney, Melbourne, Auckland
and Wellington.
</P>
<P>
He exchanged views with political and business leaders of both
countries and updated them on how the "One country, Two systems"
concept had been successfully implemented in Hong Kong since the
handover.
</P>
<P>
The Chief Executive also held talks with government leaders
there to strengthen Hong Kong's economic and trade ties with the
two countries. 
</P>
