<HEADLINE> Nigeria Enters Last 16 in World Cup Finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria entered the last 16 in the World
Cup finals after beating Bulgaria 1-0 at Parcs des Princes here on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
AS Monaco midfielder Victor Ikpeba netted the winner in close range
in the 26th minute on a short pass from Daniel Amokachi on the right,
sparking celebration among about 1,000 green-shirted Nigeraian fans in
the nearly full 40,000-seat stadium.
</P>
<P>
Ikpeba almost added another two minutes later when he made a lone
run down the left but his shot glided off the far post.
</P>
<P>
Bulgaria rallied after the break to staged a few threatening
attacks, with their best chance coming in the 87th minute when CSKA
Sofia's striker Emil Kostadinov sent a booming blast only to see the
ball hit the crossbar.
</P>
<P>
Kostadniov's Sofia teammate Hristo Stoichkov also had scoring
opportunity in the 66th minute, shotting in the area but the ball was
saved by keeper Peter Rufai.
</P>
<P>
Scorer Ipkeba said after the game, "I have to say it was a victory
for the whole team. It was a tough game and I should give credit to
all the team."
</P>
<P>
A beaming Nigerian head coach Bora Milutinovic said, "I am very
happy. But the right thing to do now is focusing on the next round."
</P>
<P>
He added, "It was a difficult game. I'm happy with the way we
played in the first half. It had been a very difficult situation for
Bulgaria because they badly needed a win."
</P>
<P>
Asked of the substitution of forwards in the second half,
Milutnovic said the motto of "the best defence is attack" was
applicable to all teams here.
</P>
<P>
"It's not only true for Nigeria, but also for all the teams," he
said.
</P>
<P>
Bulgarian coach Hristo Bonev said, "We played with balance in the
first half until the goal came. That goal really killed us for good."
</P>
<P>
Nigeria, who lost to Italy in the second round in the 1994 World
Cup finals, secured a place in the second round by leading Group D
here with six points. 
</P>
