<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania's second private
insurance company, Heritage A.I.I. Insurance Company (T) Ltd, was
launched here Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
The new insurance company is a joint venture between the MAC
Group Ltd and the well-experienced Heritage A.I.I. Insurance
Company of Kenya.
</P>
<P>
The MAC Group Ltd Chairman Yogesh Manek, told reporters at the
signing ceremony for the event that the company will "greatly
improve service and efficiency presently lacking in the insurance
sector."
</P>
<P>
The company will undertake general insurance business
including fire, marine, motor, customs bond, machinery breakdown,
compensation for workmen's injuries, medical, cash in transit,
burglary, sickness, accident, among others.
</P>
<P>
He said MAC group has a wide range of business in
manufacturing consumer and industrial goods, finance, auto
assembly, while Heritage A.I.I. Insurance Company is one of the
largest insurance companies in Kenya.
</P>
<P>
Tanzania's first private insurance company, the Jubilee
Insurance Company of Tanzania Limited, was opened earlier this
year. It is a joint venture between the Washington-based
International Finance Corporation (IFC) and the Aga Khan Fund for
Economic Development.
</P>
<P>
Legislation for opening up the insurance sector in Tanzania
was approved in February of 1997.  
