<HEADLINE> Nigeria: 700,000 Women Develop Cancer Yearly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, June 19 (Xinhua) -- About 700,000 women in Nigeria
develop breast cancer annually, the News Agency of Nigeria
reported Friday, quoting a surgeon of the country.
</P>
<P>
About 83 percent of the breast cancer patients are even at the
advanced stages of the disease and only about 15 to 20 percent
survived, said Olusola Akute, a consultant surgeon at the
University College Hospital in Ibadan, western Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
At a lecture Thursday to mark the launching of the Breast
Cancer Association of Nigeria, Akute also said that the patients'
survival after diagnosis was only for two years.
</P>
<P>
As the disease could be curable if detected early, he called
on women to always subject their breast to self-examination while
bathing and to consult medical experts if any strange lump or
discharge was noticed in their breasts.
</P>
<P>
Olusola Akute said that ignorance, financial constraints and
fear of surgery are some of the reasons that make the disease to
reach advanced stages before detection.  
</P>
</TEXT>
