<HEADLINE> Romania Benefits from Additional EU Support </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, June 19 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) will
increase the financial aid granted to the ten candidate states in
Central and Eastern Europe, the local daily Evenimentul Zilei
(Daily Events) reported Friday quoting sources with the European
Commission(EC).
</P>
<P>
According to the sources, Romania could receive a 300 million
ECU yearly supplement as of January 2000, by implementing programs
such as ISPA, SAPARD, as well as the PHARE program. ISPA is a
program to support environment and transport projects, while
SAPARD is to back farming sector development and rural areas.
</P>
<P>
The ISPA program provides a 85 percent coverage of the
projects, with the rest of the financing to come from national or
local budgets. The ISPA annual funds are forecast to hit 1 billion
ECU between 2000 and 2006U.
</P>
<P>
As for the funds granted to Romania under the PHARE program,
they will hit 150 million ECU in 1999, up from 117 million this
year. 30 percent of the PHARE funds will go to strengthen the
institutions sector, with the rest of the money to be channelled
to investments aimed to support Romania's joining the European
Union.
</P>
<P>
According to EC officials, Romania had met only one of the
three criteria for EU integration so far, namely the political
one, while the supplementation of the funds also depends on the
fulfillment of the other two criteria: an efficient market economy
and legislation in line with the EU countries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
