<HEADLINE> Preparations Start on UNITA's Handover of Four </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Preparations started Friday to
establish national authorities in the four cities in central
Angola which had been under the control of the National Union for
the Total Independence of Angola (UNITA).
</P>
<P>
The four cities are Andulo and Nharea in Bie Province, Huambo
and Mungo in Bailundo Province.
</P>
<P>
Media reports here said a joint team comprising United Nations
mission in Angola, representatives of the three observer
countries--the United States, Russia and Portugal, members of
Angolan government and UNITA in the Committee of Angolan Peace
Process as well as other senior government officials, started to
work Friday on the preparations.
</P>
<P>
An agreement on the preparatory work was reached following
difficult negotiations between the Angolan government and the
opposition UNITA with the mediation of U.N. special envoy to
Angola, Blondin Beye.
</P>
<P>
Angolan pace process was stalled for over two months due to
UNITA's refusal to hand over the four cities to the government as
stipulated in the Lusaka Peace Accord signed in 1994.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. Security Council adopted a new resolution on June 12
to impose new sanctions on the former rebel UNITA movement, which
will go into force on June 25 if the UNITA fails to make
concessions regarding this issue.  
</P>
