<HEADLINE> U.N. Sponsored Forum to Address Governance in Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, June 19 (Xinhua) -- A United Nations sponsored
forum will focus on governance accountability and transparency in
African countries, it was announced here Friday.
</P>
<P>
The forum, organized by the U.N. Development Program (UNDP) and
the Economic Commission for Africa (ECA), will be held in Accra,
Ghana, from June 25-26, Special Advisor for U.N. Special
Initiative in Africa Trevor Gordon-Sommers told reporters.
</P>
<P>
Officials of a number of African governments and donor
countries will gather to share experiences in political,
administrative, financial and budgetary accountability and in the
relationship between transparency and good governance, he said.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is actually a follow-up to the Africa Governance
Forum held in Addis Ababa in July 1997 which mandated the UNDP and
the ECA to lead the process with an anticipation that it becomes
an annual event, Gordon-Sommers said.
</P>
<P>
It will provide an opportunity for regional countries to
examine various issues along with their external partners, he
added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
