<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Sends Greetings To Scientists At South Pole </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 20 (Xinhua) -- Premier Zhu Rongji sent a cable of
greetings today for the Midwinter Festival to Chinese and foreign
scientists who are conducting scientific research at the South
Pole.
</P>
<P>
Zhu extended his sincere greetings to the scientists and
technicians on behalf of the Chinese government and the Chinese
people and wished them a happy holiday.
</P>
<P>
The South Pole is the world's only unpolluted continent, one
covered with ice and snow, Zhu said, and to reveal the mysteries
there, the scientists have made a great effort in overcoming the
difficulties of adverse climate and circumstances, and have new
research findings, giving confidence in the ability of human
beings to conquer nature.
</P>
<P>
With a common theme of peace, cooperation and friendship, the
scientists have worked for the cause of peace and development in
the world, the premier said.
</P>
<P>
Zhu congratulated them on many successes in their hard work and
wished them greater contributions to scientific research and
protecting the South Pole. 
</P>
