<HEADLINE> India's FCA Drops by 856m US dollars on June 12: RBI </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 20 (Xinhua) -- India's foreign currency assets
(FCA) dropped by 856 million U.S. dollars to 24,354 million
dollars as on June 12, according to the sources of the Reserve
Bank of India (RBI) here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Total foreign exchange reserves went down by 909 million
dollars to 27,570 million dollars, with special drawing rights
(SDR) falling by 53 million dollars to 118 million dollars, said
the RBI's weekly statistical supplement.
</P>
<P>
The fall in foreign exchange reserves has occurred in the
backdrop of RBI Governor Bimal Jalan's assertion last week that
RBI would not hesitate to use its reserves to meet the country's
external obligations and current account deficit if necessary, the
same sources said. 
</P>
