<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iraqi FM Stresses Importance of Iraq-Iran Contacts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, June 20 (Xinhua) -- Iraqi Foreign Minister Mohammed
Saeed al-Sahhaf Saturday said frequent exchange of visits by
officials between Iran and Iraq is very important to improve the
bilateral relations, the Iraqi News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
A closer contact will help reduce the differences of the two
countries and pave way for normalizing the bilateral relations,
al-Sahhaf said during a meeting with Abdullah Najafi, head of an
Iranian committee for the prisoners and the missing in war.
</P>
<P>
He underlined the need to make joint efforts to settle the
remaining issues of prisoners of war (POW) and the missing in
action (MIA) as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
Najafi expressed pleasure in visiting Iraq and voiced hope that
the joint efforts of the two sides would yield soon concrete
results and have positive effects on the bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
The issue of POW is the main obstacle to the normalization of
the Iraq-Iran ties since the end of the 1980-88 war between the
two sides.
</P>
<P>
Last April, in the biggest repatriation of POWs since 1990,
Iran released 5,584 Iraqi prisoners of war, and Iraq freed three
POWs and 316 Iranians it classified as civil law detainees.
</P>
</TEXT>
