<HEADLINE> Croatia Almost Qualify with 1-0 Win over Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
NANTES, June 20 (Xinhua) -- Croatia have almost qualified for
the round of 16 after beating Japan 1-0 in a Group H match on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
It is Croatia's second straight victory in the World Cup finals.
If Argentina beat or draw with Jamaica at Parc des Princes on
Sunday, then Croatian team will be ensured a place in the last 16.
</P>
<P>
However, the Croatians failed to produce the sparks and
brilliances they had in the match against Jamaica and in the first
half, it was the Japanese team seemed more likely to score.
</P>
<P>
After the lackluster first half which ended 0-0, the Croatians
were more aggressively in the second half. Captain Davor Suker got
a perfect pass from teammate Aljosa Asanovic at the 77th minute and
beat the Japanese goal-keeper Yoshikatsu Kawaguchi with a left-footer.
</P>
<P>
Croatia could have scored earlier in the match but the crossbar
denied the effort of Slaven Bilic.
</P>
<P>
It was the second straight defeat for Japan, who are in
desperate need of a goal in their first ever World Cup. The co-hosts
of the 2002 World Cup finals have been denied any possibilities for
qualifying for the second round though they still have a match to
play. 
</P>
</TEXT>
