<HEADLINE> Speeding Up Highway Construction In China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, June 20 (Xinhua) -- China will spend 3 billion yuan
(about 375 million U.S. dollars) to increase highway construction
in central and western parts of the country, Minister of
Communications Huang Zhengdong said here today.
</P>
<P>
Huang outlined four major steps the State Council will take
this year for this at a national meeting that opened here today.
</P>
<P>
The country will increase bus fares by one fen (about an eighth
a U.S. cent) per kilometer as of July 1st and will use the
additional money to build more highways. Some profitable toll
roads financed by the central treasury will be allowed to float
shares and try to get listed, and investment funds for toll roads
on the mainland will be traded like industrial funds on a trial
basis. 
</P>
