<HEADLINE> Chinese Seminar On Famous Dramatist </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 20 (Xinhua) -- China held a seminar in Beijing
today to mark the 100th birthday of Tian Han, a leading Chinese
dramatist.
</P>
<P>
Li Lanqing, a member of the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China,
was present, along with hundreds of Chinese officials and artists.
</P>
<P>
Ding Guangen, a member of the Political Bureau of the CPC
Central Committee and head of the CPC Central Committee Publicity
Department, said that Tian was a founder of China's revolutionary
drama movement and a pioneer in the reform of traditional opera,
and an outstanding organizer and leader of China's early
revolutionary music and film production.
</P>
<P>
Ding pointed out that Tian made a great contribution to the
country's culture and art and gained a reputation worldwide for
his artistic and literary creations.
</P>
<P>
The seminar was sponsored by the Ministry of Culture, the State
Administration of Radio, Film and Television, and the China
Literary and Art Federation. 
