<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Floods Kill 12 People In Eastern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, June 20 (Xinhua) -- Heavy rains that lashed the city of
Nanping in east China's Fujian Province from June 12 through 19
killed 12 people, injured 138, and caused serious damage to
infrastructure and housing.
</P>
<P>
The storm brought an average of 50 centimeters of rain in the
city and over 70 in four suburban counties including the scenic
spot of Mount Wuyi.
</P>
<P>
Floodwaters inundated as many as 33,900 houses, killed 360,000
head of livestock, and destroyed 17,133 hectares of crops. In the
city, 288 factories had to suspend production. Local sources
estimate losses at more then 1.55 billion yuan (about 194 million
U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The city has been hit by torrential rains three times since
early summer, pushing rivers to their limits, and local
meteorologists say the wet spell could last until June 23. 
</P>
</TEXT>
