<HEADLINE> World Cup Referees' Performance Rated </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 20 (Xinhua) -- The performance of referees in the World
Cup finals are being scored with marks on the scale of 10, a senior
member of the FIFA referees' commitee said here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Farouk Bouzo of Syria said, "I can generally tell you that the
general (average) mark is 8.1 points."
</P>
<P>
He added that the highest point was 9.0 while the lowest was only
6.4 points but declined to name who was the worst referee.
</P>
<P>
The scores would be used as evidences when the committee selects
the the referees for the second stage competition.
</P>
<P>
But he said the refereeing until now was generally good although he
admitted the referees were not free of mistakes.
</P>
<P>
"The game is game of mistakes. Players committed mistakes and
referees committed mistakes as well," Bouzo added.
</P>
<P>
He denied that the spate of red and yellow cards in Thursday's two
games were due to the earlier remarks made by FIFA President Sepp
Blatter in a news conference.
</P>
<P>
A total of five red cards were flashed in the games between Denmark
and South Africa, and between France and Saudi Arabia.
</P>
<P>
Blatter had said sanction against tackling from behind was not
carried out strictly enough.
</P>
<P>
But Bouzo said, "It was not reaction of the president's conference.
This is to protect the players, to let the game being played in a
clean way." 
</P>
