<HEADLINE> Chinese State Bank Loans For Water Control Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 20 (Xinhua) -- The State Development Bank signed
a 3.7 billion yuan (about 462 million U.S. dollars) agreement for
loans for a key water control project on the Yellow River here
today.
</P>
<P>
The Wanjiazhai Water Conservation Project on the upper reaches
of the country's second longest river involves water supply, power
supplies and prevention of ice floes.
</P>
<P>
It will be able to provide some 1.2 billion cubic meters of
water each year to three major cities in Shanxi Province and 200
cubic meters to the Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region. It will also
generate 2.75 billion kw/h of electricity for Shanxi and Inner
Mongolia.
</P>
<P>
The project started in November 1994 and will cost 6.1 billion
yuan when completed. With the SDB loans, the main part of the
project is expected to be completed by the end of this
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
