<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 20 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's Television Broadcast
Limited (TVB) has been fined 100,000 HK dollars (12,800 U.S.
dollars) for its recent broadcasting of a program featuring an
interview with an alleged Macao gang leader.
</P>
<P>
It was believed to be the third highest fine levied by Hong
Kong's Broadcasting Authority, with the maximum fine for such an
offense being 250,000 UK dollars (32,000 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The episode of Focus on Focus, broadcast on May 1 on TVB Jade,
featured Wan Kuok-koi, also known as "Broken Tooth", the alleged
leader of Macao's 14K triad society, who talked about his wealth
and success in gambling. The broadcast was followed by about 300
complaints from viewers.
</P>
<P>
"The glorification of triad members is totally objectionable
and can't be broadcast at this time," said Authority chairman
Norman Leung Nai-pang.
</P>
<P>
It sent a very wrong message that one can get rich through
triad activities, which would have a bad influence on youngsters,
he said. 
</P>
