<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Kicks Off Healthy Living Campaign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 20 (Xinhua) -- More than 7,000 people pledged
here Saturday to make Hong Kong a healthy city at the launching
ceremony of a three-year campaign called "Healthy Living Into the
21st Century."
</P>
<P>
"The promotion of people's awareness of personal and public
hygiene will enable Hong Kong to maintain its international status
as a healthy and clean cosmopolitan city," Chief Executive of the
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) Tung Chee Hwa said
while officiating at the kick-off ceremony at the Hong Kong
Coliseum.
</P>
<P>
He noted that a series of incidents of food hygiene in recent
months had underlined the need to upgrade Hong Kong's public
health and environmental hygiene.
</P>
<P>
To encourage people of all ages and from different sectors to
take part in the campaign, the SAR government will launch a series
of promotion and education activities, such as broadcasting a
50-episode "One Minute Health" program on the local radio,
cleaning the beaches and training student environmental protection
ambassadors.
</P>
<P>
The government will also accord top priority to prosecution
actions against those who break the law. "The relevant authorities
will deploy staff to take enforcement action against littering,
spitting, smoking in no-smoking areas and the operation of
unlicensed food premises," Tung added.
</P>
<P>
A steering committee on healthy living, chaired by
Administrative Secretary Anson Chan, will be responsible for the
progress of campaign. 
</P>
</TEXT>
