ankle injury in the 2-0 defeat of the United States on Monday. But
Thomas Hassler is recovering from his ankle injury and that is a
good news for the German team.
</P>
<P>
It's not clear if Vogts would let World Cup veteran Lothar Matthaus
play in the match. If Matthaus has the chance to play, he will be the
first player in history to play 22 games in World Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Yugoslavia's Sinisa Mihajlovic said he believed that
the match against Germany would be easier than against Iran.
</P>
<P>
