<HEADLINE> Vietnam Sentences Four Drug Traffickers To Death </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Four drug traffickers were sentenced
to death and three others given life imprisonment in Vietnam's
central coastal province of Ha Tinh on Friday.
</P>
<P>
A Vietnamese woman was sentenced to five years in jail,
according to the Vietnam News Agency.
</P>
<P>
The eight were charged with involvement in the province's
biggest drug trafficking ring, which smuggled a total of 49
kilograms of heroin from Laos into Vietnam between March 1996 and
April 1997.
</P>
<P>
Among the four who got death sentence, two are from Laos.
</P>
<P>
The court ordered the confiscation of 7.2 kg of heroin, two
cars and mobile phones used in the trafficking.
</P>
<P>
Last year eight other persons belonging to the country's
largest trafficking ring were sentenced to death for bringing
several hundred kilograms of heroin into Vietnam since 1992.
</P>
