<P>
Dr. Huang went on to say that both countries have the basis of
cooperation in the battles against drugs, pollution, nuclear
proliferation, as well as in alleviation of the impact of the
financial crisis in southeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
"The 20th century has been one of wars and armed conflicts, and
I hope that the coming century will be one of peace," he said,
adding that developing bilateral friendly and cooperative ties by
the means of seeking the common ground while reserving their
differences, accords with the current dominating trend in the
world.
</P>
