President Clinton's visit to China will be a significant event
as the present world is closely inter-related and has increasingly
becoming a "global village" and the countries worldwide need all
the more exchanges and cooperation among them rather than
separation of each other, said Dr. Daniel Bennett from Stanford
University, who is currently teaching at the Northwest University.
