paid-up capital of 250 billion rupiah (25 million U.S. dollars) by
the end of this year, Minister of Finance Bambang Subianto
said. "Only new banks are now obliged to meet this capital
requirement," Bambang told reporters after meeting with President
B.J. Habibie. (Indonesia-Banks) 
