<HEADLINE> Shanghai Industrial Output Increases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 20 (Xinhua) -- The latest statistics show that
Shanghai, China's economic powerhouse, registered an 8.8 percent
growth rate in industrial output dring the first five months of
this year.
</P>
<P>
During the period, the municipality completed 226.4 billion
yuan (27.3 billion US dollars) of output, according to the local
statistics bureau.
</P>
<P>
Except for the solely state-owned firms, the economic sector
increased its industrial output value.
</P>
<P>
But statistics for the four-month January-April period
reflected a profit decline because of poor sales in the industrial
sector. The profits of the sector dropped by 28.5 percent while
losses rose by 26.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
The foreign-funded firms suffered the most during the period,
affected by fewer exports under the pressure of the Southeast
Asian financial crisis, according to the bureau.
</P>
<P>
Economists said that the macro-economic measures have been
effective in preventing the economy from sliding further, but an
overall economic revival will still take time. 
</P>
