<HEADLINE> Foreign Offenders on Increase in Hungary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, June 15 (Xinhua) - The number of foreigners
committing crimes in Hungary rose four percent to 4,923 last year,
according to Hungarian government statistics.
</P>
<P>
Romanians were the leading foreign offenders -- 1,818 were
charged with offences -- followed by Yugoslavians, Ukrainians,
Germans, Austrians and Chinese.
</P>
<P>
Property offences, public order and traffic disturbances were
the main areas in which foreigners were charged.
</P>
<P>
Crimes by foreigners made up two percent of the total crimes
committed in Hungary last year. Outside Hungary, 137 Hungarians
committed crimes last year, statistics showed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
