<HEADLINE> Guangzhou to Invest 5.1 Billion U.S.dollars in Key Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 20 (Xinhua) -- The provincial capital of south
China's Guangdong province plans to invest 42.3 billion yuan (5.1
billion U.S. dollars) to construct 13 key projects in the coming
years, today's China Daily reported.
</P>
<P>
Guo Xiling, director of the Guangzhou Planning Commission, said
that a total of 11.2 billion yuan (1.35 billion U.S. dollars) will
be used this year.
</P>
<P>
The first phase of Xinsha Port, Zhujiang Steel Production Base,
which include expansion of Zhujiang Steel Plant and Guangzhou
Steelworks, and completion of Guangzhou Metro Line One, are on top
of the list, Guo said.
</P>
<P>
Other projects include Guangzhou New International Airport;
Guangzhou Automobile Project, a joint venture with Honda of Japan;
Huancheng Expressway; Liede Sewage Treatment Plant; Wuyang Honda
Motor Project; an agricultural zone for experimental good quality,
high efficiency, high yield farming techniques in the city's
Baiyun District; Guangzhou Art Museum; Guangzhou Paper Mill; and
Computer Industrial Town inside Guangzhou Free Trade Zone.
</P>
<P>
Line One of Guangzhou Metro will help ease the city's
worsening traffic jams, while construction will begin on the new
international airport, Guo said at the Municipal People's Congress
which opened on June 17.  
