<HEADLINE> World Bank Loans Help Agriculture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 20 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank on Thursday
approved two loans totalling 600 million U.S.dollars to help China
increase agricultural production and rural electrical service,
today's China Daily reported.
</P>
<P>
The money will be used for building and improving irrigation
systems and farmland in China's Yellow-Huaihe-Rivers-Plain. A
power development project in central-south China's Hunan Province
will also get some of the money.
</P>
<P>
The irrigation project will cover five provinces, namely Hebei,
Henan, Shandong, Jiangxi and Anhui provinces. The project will
promote food security, irrigate reform and environmental
protection of major lakes and ground water in the project area.
</P>
<P>
The main components of the project include construction and
rehabilitation of farmland irrigation distribution installations;
land leveling and improvement and soil enhancement; establishment
of shelter-forest networks for farmland; expansion of rural road
and electric networks for farmland; expansion of rural road and
electric networks; procurement of agricultural production
materials and support of agricultural institutional development.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Chinese Government will contribute 300 million
U.S. dollars to the 849.3 million U.S. dollars project.  
</P>
</TEXT>
