<HEADLINE> New Panamanian Law Protect Foreign Investors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Foreign investors will now be
fully protected by a new Panamanian law, enjoying free
repatriation of capital, dividends, interest and profits gained
from their investments.
</P>
<P>
The law, approved by the National Legislative Assembly on
Thursday, will also help promote foreign investments in all the
sectors of the Panamanian economy.
</P>
<P>
Treated as their Panamanian peers, foreign businessmen will be
able to invest in the country's tourism, industry, agriculture,
forestry, mining and other ventures.
</P>
<P>
To closely monitor the strict application of the new law, the
Panamanian government set up a consultative council of juridical
stability. 
</P>
