<DOCNO> XIE19980620.0208 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fuzhou Development Zone Attracts More Overseas Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, June 20 (Xinhua) -- A state-level development zone in
this capital of east China's Fujian Province has been successful
in minimizing the effects of the Asian financial crisis and drawn
more overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
Fifty-three overseas-funded projects were approved in the
Fuzhou Development Zone in the first five months of this year,
with total investment and contracted overseas investment valued at
300 million US dollars and 230 million US dollars,
respectively. All three figures were considerably larger than
their counterparts for the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
To cope with the effects of the Asian financial crisis, the
zone authorities have readjusted their strategy to attract
overseas investment, particularly increasing the effort to draw
investment from Japan, Europe and the United States.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, they attached keen importance to spreading investment
information and launched several investment fairs.
</P>
<P>
As part of its effort to improve the soft investment
environment, the zone rectified related administrative fees and
introduced preferential rates to the maximum extent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
