<HEADLINE> S. Africa Says Trade Minister Not WTO Chief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 19 (Xinhua) -- South Africa has no
intention of nominating its Trade and Industry Minister Alec
Erwin or any one of its nationals to the position of
Director-General of the World Trade Organization (WTO), a Foreign
Ministry spokesman said Friday night.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman was reacting to news reports that Erwin is in
line for the WTO top job after WTO Director-General, Renato
Ruggiero, indicated that he will not seek a second term.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said the rumors are unfounded, the South African
Press Association reported.
</P>
<P>
Business Day newspaper Monday quoted Reuter as saying that
Erwin is a candidate along with former New Zealand prime minister
Michael Moore, former Canadian Trade Minister Bruce MacLaren, and
Brazilian Foreign Minister Luiz Lampreia.  
</P>
</TEXT>
