<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Paraguay Hold Spain to Goalless Draw </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
SAINT-ETIENNE, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Paraguay held Spain to a
disappointing goalless draw in a Group D match here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Spanish coach Javier Clemente made five changes to his
starting line-up in the match against Nigerian which they lost 3-2.
But the Spanish team appeared nervous in the first half and could
not find a way to break up the tight defence of the Paraguay team.
</P>
<P>
The second half was more exciting as the Spanish team went all out
for attack while the Paraguay team time and again luanched
counter-attacks which posed real threat to the Spanish goal.
</P>
<P>
The Spanish forwards, without the effective support from the
midfield, seldom got the shooting chances in the packed Paraguay
area and the draw further jeoperdized their qualifying chances.
</P>
<P>
The Spanish team garnered only one point after two matches and
must beat Bulgaria in their last group match to keep their
quliifying hopes alive.
</P>
<P>
But if the Nigerian team, which secured the top place of the
group due to the Paraguay-Spain draw, lose to Paraguay in their
encounter, the Spaniards will still be eliminated.
</P>
<P>
Spain were regarded by many people as one of the five favorites
of the World Cup finals before the tournament kicked off on June 10.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
