<HEADLINE> Norway Could Beat Brazil: Coach </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LA BOULE, France, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Norway could have a chance to
beat defending champion Brazil in their last group A match, Norway
coach Egil Olsen said on Friday.
</P>
<P>
"If we defend well it's not impossible to beat Brazil as our
strikers are good," said Olsen in the team's camp in
Saint-Andre-des-Eaux.
</P>
<P>
He said his team had had five scoring chances in their last game
against Scotland on Tuesday, which indicated their strength in
offense.
</P>
<P>
"I can say we went fairly well then. When the intensity and
aggressiveness goes in the midfield, which is what happened, our whole
defensive system pays the price."
</P>
<P>
He added that several players, including Chelsea forward Tore Andre
Flo, had failed to give their best.
</P>
<P>
"We've worked hard in training to correct these gaps and we can
legitimately hope for a win," he concluded. 
</P>
